She was in charge of Hynic Core,

762
00:43:34,070 --> 00:43:36,197
but her access
to all information was revoked,

763
00:43:36,280 --> 00:43:38,157
and she was taken off the case overnight.

764
00:43:38,241 --> 00:43:41,244
That coincides with the time
Bluestone proposed that loan to you.

765
00:43:42,829 --> 00:43:45,706
Now all the pieces are falling into place.

766
00:43:46,249 --> 00:43:48,292
Did you bring
your contract with Bluestone?

767
00:43:48,376 --> 00:43:49,418
Yes.

768
00:43:51,337 --> 00:43:53,214
Here you go.

769
00:43:53,714 --> 00:43:55,216
I'll take a close look.

770
00:44:05,810 --> 00:44:06,811
Hello?

771
00:44:07,645 --> 00:44:10,648
Yes, that's me. How can I help you?

772
00:44:12,733 --> 00:44:13,943
What?

773
00:44:14,527 --> 00:44:16,404
Someone impersonated me?

774
00:44:17,738 --> 00:44:20,491
Okay. I'm on my way.

775
00:44:21,868 --> 00:44:23,119
Did something happen?

776
00:44:23,202 --> 00:44:26,497
The police want me to come in
for questioning as a witness

777
00:44:26,581 --> 00:44:28,541
in a fraud case
where someone impersonated me.

778
00:44:28,624 --> 00:44:29,542
- What?
- What?

779
00:44:31,127 --> 00:44:34,046
Dr. Choi is scheduled to appear
before the prosecution this afternoon.

780
00:44:34,130 --> 00:44:35,173
Yes.

781
00:44:35,840 --> 00:44:37,550
I could end up being late,

782
00:44:37,633 --> 00:44:39,802
so I'll let Mr. Yoon know before I leave.

783
00:44:39,886 --> 00:44:41,846
- Sure. Get going.
- Okay.

784
00:44:42,346 --> 00:44:43,931
I hope it's nothing serious.

785
00:44:51,731 --> 00:44:53,482
Are they still questioning her?

786
00:44:55,735 --> 00:44:57,820
Shouldn't we go down to the station?

787
00:44:57,904 --> 00:44:59,071
She's just a witness.

788
00:44:59,155 --> 00:45:01,073
- You know something, don't you?
- No, I don't.

789
00:45:02,074 --> 00:45:04,911
I think you do.
You two seem pretty close recently.

790
00:45:05,912 --> 00:45:07,538
Is there anything we can do to help?

791
00:45:09,207 --> 00:45:12,335
We need to know what's going on
to come up with a plan.

792
00:45:14,212 --> 00:45:16,005
I need to get going.

793
00:45:16,088 --> 00:45:16,964
Where?

794
00:45:17,590 --> 00:45:20,384
Dr. Choi is scheduled
to appear before the prosecution today.

795
00:45:20,468 --> 00:45:22,845
Right. You're accompanying her
as legal counsel.

796
00:45:23,596 --> 00:45:24,764
Yeah.

797
00:45:28,601 --> 00:45:30,686
Did you hear from Ms. Choi?

798
00:45:30,770 --> 00:45:31,896
Nothing yet.

799
00:45:32,980 --> 00:45:34,565
- Let's take my car.
- Okay.

800
00:45:37,401 --> 00:45:39,946
You can't reach her, right?

801
00:45:46,661 --> 00:45:49,622
I saw the opinion brief.
It was quite thorough.

802
00:45:49,705 --> 00:45:51,749
Yes, all thanks to--

803
00:45:57,880 --> 00:45:58,965
Dr. Choi Ji-su.

804
00:45:59,674 --> 00:46:02,093
Did you intentionally kill
Mr. Kim Byeong-su?

805
00:46:02,593 --> 00:46:05,096
No… I didn't.

806
00:46:06,305 --> 00:46:07,431
All right.

807
00:46:08,015 --> 00:46:09,892
You will not be indicted for murder.

808
00:46:11,018 --> 00:46:11,894
Pardon?

809
00:46:12,520 --> 00:46:15,856
The brief outlined very clearly
that you didn't kill Mr. Kim Byeong-su.

810
00:46:15,940 --> 00:46:17,233
I see.

811
00:46:17,316 --> 00:46:19,777
Since we had a dead prick on our hands,

812
00:46:20,569 --> 00:46:24,031
we considered indicting for manslaughter
due to occupational negligence,

813
00:46:24,115 --> 00:46:25,992
but the autopsy concluded

814
00:46:26,826 --> 00:46:29,912
that the cause of death
was aortic dissection,

815
00:46:29,996 --> 00:46:32,248
caused by vascular Ehlers-Danlos syndrome,

816
00:46:32,331 --> 00:46:33,916
an underlying condition.

817
00:46:34,417 --> 00:46:36,836
Yes, we agree with that as well.

818
00:46:36,919 --> 00:46:40,047
The brief includes the analysis
of a pathology expert.

819
00:46:40,131 --> 00:46:41,757
Yes, I reviewed that.

820
00:46:42,383 --> 00:46:46,095
After reviewing the autopsy results
and the submitted opinion brief,

821
00:46:47,638 --> 00:46:49,015
we have concluded there was

822
00:46:49,098 --> 00:46:52,143
no direct causal link
between the emergency care and death.

823
00:46:57,064 --> 00:46:58,065
Dr. Choi Ji-su.

824
00:46:59,984 --> 00:47:02,570
We have decided not to pursue
indictment in this case.

825
00:47:04,655 --> 00:47:05,531
Really?

826
00:47:06,157 --> 00:47:09,035
Yes. This investigation is closed.
You may leave.

827
00:47:10,244 --> 00:47:13,247
Thank you for taking the time
to come all the way here today.

828
00:47:13,748 --> 00:47:14,874
Get back safely.

829
00:47:15,499 --> 00:47:17,585
Yes. Thank you.

830
00:47:28,429 --> 00:47:30,931
Is it all over now?

831
00:47:31,724 --> 00:47:32,600
Yes.

832
00:47:33,100 --> 00:47:36,145
They decided on non-indictment,
so this concludes the case.

833
00:47:36,645 --> 00:47:37,730
Thank goodness.

834
00:47:38,314 --> 00:47:40,941
Thank you so much, both of you.

835
00:47:41,025 --> 00:47:42,735
Thank you for working so hard.

836
00:47:42,818 --> 00:47:45,738
You can stop worrying now.
Get plenty of rest.

837
00:47:46,364 --> 00:47:48,407
Okay. Thank you.

838
00:47:56,665 --> 00:47:57,792
They decided not to indict.

839
00:47:59,251 --> 00:48:01,879
We did work hard on the opinion brief,

840
00:48:02,463 --> 00:48:05,257
but I wasn't expecting them
to decide against indictment.

841
00:48:06,425 --> 00:48:07,343
CHOI HO-YEON

842
00:48:08,594 --> 00:48:09,553
It's Ms. Choi.

843
00:48:10,179 --> 00:48:11,097
Hello?

844
00:48:11,639 --> 00:48:12,890
What happened?

845
00:48:15,142 --> 00:48:16,477
Oh, really?

846
00:48:18,521 --> 00:48:19,480
All right.

847
00:48:20,231 --> 00:48:21,982
It's okay.

848
00:48:22,608 --> 00:48:25,152
Don't worry. Okay, bye.

849
00:48:27,947 --> 00:48:28,906
What did she say?

850
00:48:29,907 --> 00:48:32,785
She's still being questioned.
Some sort of misunderstanding.

851
00:48:33,661 --> 00:48:34,537
I see.

852
00:48:34,620 --> 00:48:37,206
I think I need to head to Ms. Choi's.

853
00:48:38,374 --> 00:48:39,250
Why?

854
00:48:39,333 --> 00:48:41,794
The kids are on break,
and her aunt is away.

855
00:48:41,877 --> 00:48:43,879
I guess they've been home alone all day.

856
00:48:44,463 --> 00:48:47,133
She mentioned she wasn't sure
if they had a proper meal yet.

857
00:48:47,216 --> 00:48:48,926
Did she say they were seven?

858
00:48:49,009 --> 00:48:49,927
Yes.

859
00:48:50,803 --> 00:48:51,720
And their parents?

860
00:48:51,804 --> 00:48:55,599
It seemed like Ms. Choi
is taking care of them on her own.

861
00:48:56,267 --> 00:48:58,310
She did say her aunt lives nearby
and helps out.

862
00:48:58,394 --> 00:48:59,437
Tell me her address.

863
00:48:59,520 --> 00:49:02,314
If you just drop me off here,
I can take a cab.

864
00:49:02,940 --> 00:49:05,901
They must be hungry. Take this car.
Don't make them wait longer.

865
00:49:24,044 --> 00:49:25,087
I think we're almost there.

866
00:49:25,171 --> 00:49:28,674
Yes, we are.
But you have to take the stairs from here.

867
00:49:28,757 --> 00:49:30,843
This is as far as we can go by car.

868
00:49:32,052 --> 00:49:35,055
Okay. We'll get out here,
and please wait for us nearby.

869
00:49:35,139 --> 00:49:36,140
You're coming too?

870
00:49:36,223 --> 00:49:37,600
Yes.

871
00:49:37,683 --> 00:49:39,185
- You don't have to--
- Let's go.

872
00:50:00,164 --> 00:50:01,373
Who is it?

873
00:50:02,374 --> 00:50:03,667
I'm Choi Ho-yeon's…

874
00:50:04,502 --> 00:50:06,337
I mean,

875
00:50:07,129 --> 00:50:08,714
I'm your sister's friend.

876
00:50:09,381 --> 00:50:11,842
Our sister doesn't have any friends.

877
00:50:12,384 --> 00:50:13,719
Well,

878
00:50:14,220 --> 00:50:16,972
I'm your sister's work friend.

879
00:50:17,056 --> 00:50:19,391
She's not home right now.

880
00:50:19,475 --> 00:50:21,393
Don't tell her that.

881
00:50:21,477 --> 00:50:25,856
She told us not to tell strangers
if there were no adults at home.

882
00:50:26,482 --> 00:50:30,361
Our sister just stepped out,

883
00:50:31,028 --> 00:50:32,613
but she's nearby.

884
00:50:32,696 --> 00:50:35,157
No, I'm here because

885
00:50:35,241 --> 00:50:37,368
she told me
she was going to be a bit late

886
00:50:37,451 --> 00:50:39,995
and she asked me to look after you girls.

887
00:50:40,079 --> 00:50:42,164
I'm here because your sister asked me to.

888
00:50:43,082 --> 00:50:44,750
Give us the password.

889
00:50:44,833 --> 00:50:45,834
Chocolate milk.

890
00:50:47,962 --> 00:50:48,921
What was that?

891
00:50:49,505 --> 00:50:51,507
Ms. Choi told me earlier.

892
00:50:51,590 --> 00:50:53,717
She said the kids might ask.

893
00:50:55,302 --> 00:50:56,303
Chocolate milk.

894
00:51:02,643 --> 00:51:03,644
Hello.

895
00:51:05,104 --> 00:51:07,648
Is he my sister's friend too?

896
00:51:08,816 --> 00:51:09,817
No.

897
00:51:09,900 --> 00:51:11,527
He's not a friend.

898
00:51:12,820 --> 00:51:14,280
He's actually her boss.

899
00:51:14,363 --> 00:51:15,614
I see.

900
00:51:15,698 --> 00:51:18,617
You must be that scary Boss Man.

901
00:51:20,452 --> 00:51:21,579
I was never scary.

902
00:51:24,999 --> 00:51:26,125
What are your names?

903
00:51:26,750 --> 00:51:28,085
I'm Choi Mi-yeon.

904
00:51:28,168 --> 00:51:30,588
- She's my younger sister.
- Choi Seo-yeon.

905
00:51:30,671 --> 00:51:31,880
Have you eaten anything?

906
00:51:33,173 --> 00:51:35,718
- You must be hungry.
- What do you want to eat?

907
00:51:35,801 --> 00:51:37,052
- Pizza.
- Stir-fried rice cake.

908
00:51:37,136 --> 00:51:38,304
- Fried chicken.
- Spaghetti.

909
00:51:38,387 --> 00:51:39,597
Grilled ribs.

910
00:51:39,680 --> 00:51:41,015
We can't have that.

911
00:51:41,557 --> 00:51:44,518
Ho-yeon said we can have grilled ribs

912
00:51:45,144 --> 00:51:47,646
only once a year during Chuseok.

913
00:51:48,731 --> 00:51:51,900
Then how about we go out
for dinner today?

914
00:51:51,984 --> 00:51:53,068
- Yes!
- Yes!

915
00:51:54,987 --> 00:51:56,030
Let's go.

916
00:51:56,113 --> 00:51:57,364
- Let's go.
- Come on.

917
00:52:12,504 --> 00:52:13,464
This place is good.

918
00:52:13,547 --> 00:52:15,299
This place is the real deal.

919
00:52:16,383 --> 00:52:17,259
You like it?

920
00:52:17,885 --> 00:52:19,887
It's so good.

921
00:52:22,014 --> 00:52:23,599
Eat up, you two.

922
00:52:26,977 --> 00:52:28,812
What's wrong? Have some more.

923
00:52:28,896 --> 00:52:30,064
I'm full.

924
00:52:30,856 --> 00:52:32,024
What? Already?

925
00:52:37,821 --> 00:52:39,823
I'm done eating too.

926
00:52:39,907 --> 00:52:41,659
Why? Have some more.

927
00:52:41,742 --> 00:52:43,118
No, thanks.

928
00:52:43,202 --> 00:52:44,536
But…

929
00:52:45,913 --> 00:52:49,750
can we bring
the leftover pork cutlets home?

930
00:52:51,418 --> 00:52:52,294
Why?

931
00:52:52,378 --> 00:52:55,255
Ho-yeon likes pork cutlets too.

932
00:52:55,339 --> 00:52:59,843
Last time we were here,
she pretended to have a stomachache

933
00:52:59,927 --> 00:53:03,389
so that we could eat
as much as we wanted.

934
00:53:03,472 --> 00:53:07,518
I knew she was pretending,

935
00:53:07,601 --> 00:53:10,354
but it was so good,

936
00:53:10,437 --> 00:53:12,940
I ended up finishing it by myself.

937
00:53:15,734 --> 00:53:18,153
You can finish yours,
and we can order some more to go.

938
00:53:18,237 --> 00:53:20,656
- Can we really?
- Of course.

939
00:53:20,739 --> 00:53:23,909
I'll be sure to buy your sister
lots of tasty food at work.

940
00:53:23,992 --> 00:53:25,536
Wow, really?

941
00:53:25,619 --> 00:53:27,246
- Yeah.
- Promise.

942
00:53:27,329 --> 00:53:28,622
Me too.

943
00:53:28,706 --> 00:53:30,249
Sure. I promise.

944
00:53:30,791 --> 00:53:32,543
Sign it.

945
00:53:34,837 --> 00:53:36,547
I wish someone else were here to see this.

946
00:53:36,630 --> 00:53:39,299
It's like your eyes
are shooting out hearts right now.

947
00:53:39,883 --> 00:53:41,927
How did you hide this side of you
for so long?

948
00:53:52,312 --> 00:53:53,897
Just put whatever you want in the cart.

949
00:53:58,110 --> 00:54:01,321
Meal kits would be best
for the kids, right?

950
00:54:01,405 --> 00:54:04,158
Yes, we should get
some side dishes as well.

951
00:54:04,241 --> 00:54:05,117
Okay.

952
00:54:14,543 --> 00:54:17,337
Make sure to eat well
even when your sister's not home.

953
00:54:17,421 --> 00:54:21,467
- You know how to make this, right?
- Yes, two minutes in the microwave.

954
00:54:21,550 --> 00:54:23,135
Four minutes for two of them.

955
00:54:23,218 --> 00:54:26,555
Right. You can have it
with the side dishes.

956
00:54:26,638 --> 00:54:29,057
And portion out the side dishes,
even if it's a hassle.

957
00:54:29,141 --> 00:54:30,058
- Okay.
- Okay.

958
00:54:32,352 --> 00:54:33,437
Here.

959
00:54:35,147 --> 00:54:37,149
Ms. Choi is running a bit late.

960
00:54:37,775 --> 00:54:39,193
Yes, she is.

961
00:54:39,693 --> 00:54:42,279
I'm heading out now.
I trust you'll put them to bed.

962
00:54:42,362 --> 00:54:44,364
- Okay.
- I'm leaving.

963
00:54:57,002 --> 00:55:00,214
Stay strong and take care.
Don't forget to listen to your sister.

964
00:55:01,298 --> 00:55:02,883
Don't leave.

965
00:55:03,509 --> 00:55:05,385
Just stay a bit longer.

966
00:55:06,887 --> 00:55:09,681
Why don't you leave
after they've gone to bed?

967
00:55:18,816 --> 00:55:20,442
I guess we grew on them already.

968
00:55:22,736 --> 00:55:24,112
They're hungry for affection.

969
00:55:28,158 --> 00:55:29,827
They're like little angels.

970
00:55:31,328 --> 00:55:34,039
They're seven, but they're still babies.

971
00:55:35,874 --> 00:55:37,960
Kim Byeong-su doesn't deserve

972
00:55:39,086 --> 00:55:41,129
to be forgiven, even in death.

973
00:55:45,467 --> 00:55:48,011
The non-indictment decision today…

974
00:55:48,804 --> 00:55:50,931
It was the outcome I was hoping for,

975
00:55:51,014 --> 00:55:54,935
but we prepared for a battle
and won before it ever started.

976
00:55:55,018 --> 00:55:57,187
It's cathartic and all,

977
00:55:57,771 --> 00:55:58,730
but the catharsis

978
00:55:59,356 --> 00:56:02,442
feels a bit underwhelming.

979
00:56:03,819 --> 00:56:06,572
Do you think Dr. Choi was lucky?

980
00:56:09,491 --> 00:56:10,909
Do you think it was luck?

981
00:56:19,626 --> 00:56:20,586
<i>No.</i>

982
00:56:21,503 --> 00:56:23,171
<i>I don't think it was luck.</i>

983
00:56:25,465 --> 00:56:29,052
I've assigned the Kim Byeong-su case
to you, Prosecutor Kwon.

984
00:56:29,136 --> 00:56:32,472
But he also handled
Kim Byeong-su's child sexual assault case.

985
00:56:33,974 --> 00:56:34,850
So?

986
00:56:35,559 --> 00:56:36,435
What's the issue?

987
00:56:39,104 --> 00:56:40,898
<i>All those who made</i>

988
00:56:40,981 --> 00:56:43,942
<i>even the smallest gesture or decision</i>
<i>to bring about Choi Ji-su's acquittal</i>

989
00:56:44,026 --> 00:56:45,777
<i>had been quietly</i>
<i>debating the right to life</i>

990
00:56:45,861 --> 00:56:48,947
<i>through the trials taking place</i>
<i>in the hidden corners of their hearts.</i>

991
00:56:49,031 --> 00:56:50,449
I will handle this case.

992
00:56:50,949 --> 00:56:53,577
How can the same prosecutor
take on this case?

993
00:56:54,119 --> 00:56:56,079
This is ridiculous.

994
00:56:56,163 --> 00:56:58,832
You will be so…

995
00:56:59,625 --> 00:57:02,210
- Biased.
- Right. Biased.

996
00:57:02,836 --> 00:57:06,214
Prosecutors do not allow
their emotions to interfere with cases.

997
00:57:06,298 --> 00:57:08,300
We are guided solely
by the law and principles.

998
00:57:09,134 --> 00:57:12,512
Unbelievable. Listen, Mister Prosecutor.

999
00:57:13,138 --> 00:57:15,265
You're clearly on that wench's side.

1000
00:57:15,349 --> 00:57:17,434
Watch your words.

1001
00:57:17,517 --> 00:57:19,394
If you want to throw a tantrum,

1002
00:57:19,478 --> 00:57:21,688
pick the right time
and the right audience.

1003
00:57:22,689 --> 00:57:25,400
<i>There was one driving force</i>
<i>behind their secret trials.</i>

1004
00:57:26,234 --> 00:57:28,445
<i>It was love for the victim, Min-sol.</i>

1005
00:57:28,528 --> 00:57:31,782
Please make sure
she gets charged with murder.

1006
00:57:31,865 --> 00:57:33,992
All right. I understand.

1007
00:57:34,076 --> 00:57:37,120
I think Mr. Kim Do-yeon
would be perfect for this case.

1008
00:57:37,204 --> 00:57:38,956
I'll have him handle your case.

1009
00:57:39,665 --> 00:57:41,708
He's good, right?

1010
00:57:41,792 --> 00:57:45,671
<i>Born from the regret and sense</i>
<i>of responsibility of the adults who failed</i>

1011
00:57:45,754 --> 00:57:49,424
<i>to protect the children who deserved</i>
<i>to grow up with love and care.</i>

1012
00:57:50,300 --> 00:57:51,301
<i>A sort of belated love.</i>

1013
00:57:51,385 --> 00:57:55,305
I never thought I'd see the day
Mr. Kim got assigned a case.

1014
00:57:55,389 --> 00:57:58,225
He can't do nothing forever
just because he's incompetent and lazy.

1015
00:57:58,308 --> 00:57:59,685
But what if he fails miserably?

1016
00:57:59,768 --> 00:58:02,229
You heard them.
The victim was Kim Byeong-su.

1017
00:58:03,563 --> 00:58:07,776
<i>And their rulings</i>
<i>were fueled by rage at the one</i>

1018
00:58:08,276 --> 00:58:10,112
<i>who destroyed that child's life.</i>

1019
00:58:10,946 --> 00:58:12,614
Once family medical history is confirmed,

1020
00:58:12,698 --> 00:58:15,200
his underlying condition
can be concluded as the cause of death.

1021
00:58:15,283 --> 00:58:19,162
<i>It didn't matter if Kim Byeong-su's death</i>
<i>was intentional or accidental.</i>

1022
00:58:19,246 --> 00:58:20,747
<i>What mattered to them</i>

1023
00:58:21,248 --> 00:58:25,711
<i>was the fact that his existence</i>
<i>remained an open wound for Min-sol.</i>

1024
00:58:27,546 --> 00:58:31,883
I know we have to work hard to ensure
that no wrongful death is overlooked,

1025
00:58:32,467 --> 00:58:34,094
but it almost feels like

1026
00:58:34,177 --> 00:58:36,555
you're all working especially hard
on this case.

1027
00:58:37,347 --> 00:58:39,766
Do you know whose autopsy this is?

1028
00:58:39,850 --> 00:58:42,102
- No.
- It's Kim Byeong-su.

1029
00:58:42,978 --> 00:58:44,146
We need to work hard.

1030
00:58:44,771 --> 00:58:45,647
Yes, we do.

1031
00:58:45,731 --> 00:58:46,940
<i>And in the end,</i>

1032
00:58:47,441 --> 00:58:49,109
<i>that sentiment became an earnest plea</i>

1033
00:58:49,192 --> 00:58:51,486
<i>for the acquittal of the one</i>
<i>who may have taken his life.</i>

1034
00:58:51,570 --> 00:58:55,240
Was Dr. Choi also aware
of Kim Byeong-su's underlying condition?

1035
00:58:55,323 --> 00:58:56,199
No.

1036
00:58:56,700 --> 00:58:59,536
Dr. Choi refused to treat him at the time.

1037
00:58:59,619 --> 00:59:02,164
She never had a chance
to check Kim Byeong-su's condition.

1038
00:59:03,331 --> 00:59:04,624
That makes sense.

1039
00:59:05,375 --> 00:59:07,961
If she had, she could be indicted
for negligent manslaughter

1040
00:59:08,045 --> 00:59:10,964
or even murder in the worst-case scenario.

1041
00:59:11,048 --> 00:59:11,923
Right.

1042
00:59:14,301 --> 00:59:17,054
There's a very good chance
the prosecution

1043
00:59:17,137 --> 00:59:19,681
and the opposing counsel
will ask you the same question.

1044
00:59:19,765 --> 00:59:20,849
I'll keep that in mind.

1045
00:59:21,683 --> 00:59:22,559
All right.

1046
00:59:23,268 --> 00:59:24,853
- Pardon?
- You didn't know.

1047
00:59:25,353 --> 00:59:28,440
You never had a chance
to examine Kim Byeong-su. Right?

1048
00:59:30,317 --> 00:59:33,070
That's how I'll answer if anyone asks me.

1049
00:59:33,153 --> 00:59:34,154
Because that's the truth.

1050
00:59:40,410 --> 00:59:41,870
I also have two daughters.

1051
00:59:41,953 --> 00:59:45,123
I knew that he had
an underlying condition five years ago,

1052
00:59:45,207 --> 00:59:46,833
but I didn't tell him.

1053
00:59:48,376 --> 00:59:51,671
I just wanted fate
to have its way with him.

1054
00:59:57,135 --> 00:59:59,930
You know such disclosure before indictment
is at our discretion, right?

1055
01:00:00,013 --> 01:00:00,889
Yes.

1056
01:00:01,848 --> 01:00:03,475
We would <i>really</i> appreciate it.

1057
01:00:06,228 --> 01:00:07,187
I'll think about it.

1058
01:00:08,814 --> 01:00:10,107
Thank you.

1059
01:00:12,984 --> 01:00:15,028
Why are you in such a hurry to leave?

1060
01:00:24,329 --> 01:00:26,748
I didn't say I'd think about it for long.

1061
01:00:26,832 --> 01:00:29,501
I assume you know
how to submit a request for access.

1062
01:00:31,711 --> 01:00:32,754
Of course.

1063
01:00:32,838 --> 01:00:34,589
Then submit a request today.

1064
01:00:34,673 --> 01:00:35,799
Okay.

1065
01:00:38,385 --> 01:00:41,805
Where did that insightful book

1066
01:00:41,888 --> 01:00:44,558
about Ehlers-Danlos syndrome go?

1067
01:00:47,561 --> 01:00:48,562
Here it is.

1068
01:00:50,480 --> 01:00:52,607
<i>In the end, his death…</i>

1069
01:00:52,691 --> 01:00:53,942
SYMPTOM-BASED VASCULAR EDS

1070
01:00:54,025 --> 01:00:57,821
<i>…simply brought a little justice</i>
<i>into the world.</i>

1071
01:00:58,405 --> 01:00:59,614
<i>Do you think</i>

1072
01:01:00,448 --> 01:01:03,034
humans have a right to life?

1073
01:01:03,785 --> 01:01:05,120
Yes, I do.

1074
01:01:07,289 --> 01:01:08,790
I believe that right

1075
01:01:09,374 --> 01:01:13,295
is determined by the marks
we make on the lives of others.

1076
01:01:14,546 --> 01:01:16,047
If that mark

1077
01:01:17,591 --> 01:01:19,467
only contains suffering and despair,

1078
01:01:21,803 --> 01:01:23,972
I think you lose the right to life.

1079
01:01:24,055 --> 01:01:26,308
And if someone who lost that right dies,

1080
01:01:27,767 --> 01:01:29,186
their death is no longer a tragedy.

1081
01:01:30,061 --> 01:01:33,440
It just becomes another piece
that keeps the world in balance.

1082
01:01:34,065 --> 01:01:36,651
How twisted must his life have been

1083
01:01:36,735 --> 01:01:38,153
for people

1084
01:01:39,613 --> 01:01:43,366
to seek justice even after his death?

1085
01:01:46,036 --> 01:01:49,372
Hamjji is on my side.

1086
01:01:50,498 --> 01:01:52,125
No.

1087
01:01:52,209 --> 01:01:54,336
Hamjji

1088
01:01:55,128 --> 01:01:57,464
is on my side.

1089
01:02:03,803 --> 01:02:05,055
You're smiling again.

1090
01:02:59,484 --> 01:03:02,779
BEYOND THE BAR

1091
01:03:04,990 --> 01:03:06,866
Ms. Kang Hyo-min is here.

1092
01:03:06,950 --> 01:03:08,702
<i>Have we met before?</i>

1093
01:03:08,785 --> 01:03:10,161
<i>I knew you wouldn't remember me.</i>

1094
01:03:10,245 --> 01:03:11,538
PTSD?

1095
01:03:13,415 --> 01:03:15,041
<i>I was a victim of severe school bullying.</i>

1096
01:03:15,125 --> 01:03:17,335
<i>But do you think Mr. Ko</i>
<i>really planned all this?</i>

1097
01:03:17,419 --> 01:03:19,462
There's no way
he would've left any evidence.

1098
01:03:19,546 --> 01:03:21,923
<i>I might just have the answer.</i>

1099
01:03:22,841 --> 01:03:26,052
<i>How dare you represent</i>
<i>the murderer who killed my daughter?</i>

1100
01:03:26,136 --> 01:03:27,887
I'm going to do my best.

1101
01:03:27,971 --> 01:03:29,764
Now it's time to find the final blow.

1102
01:03:29,848 --> 01:03:30,765
This is it.

